{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1591276420,"nonce":"DOZcROj4rTlrJi2N/W+yimkoB38=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2MzA4MDkyNjQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3060","origin":"github"},"title":"EMBOSS tools improperly sanitize regular expression input","message":"originally reported here https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-devteam/issues/405\n\nEMBOSS tools such as `dreg` improperly sanitize the regex input, often resulting in useless regular expressions. E.g. `AC[TG]` becomes `AC__ob__TG__cb__`.\n\nThis should likely be fixed by adding a `\u003csanitizer\u003e` tag to the tools XML: https://docs.galaxyproject.org/en/latest/dev/schema.html#tool|inputs|param|sanitizer\n\nFor reference, here is a complete list of characters used by dreg regexps: http://emboss.sourceforge.net/apps/release/6.6/emboss/apps/dreg.html\n\nThanks to @nsoranzo for helping dig into this issue.","files":null}]}